text: Sean R. Parnell (born November 19, 1962) is an American politician. He served as the 12th Governor of Alaska from 2009 to 2014. Parnell assumed the office of governor on July 26, 2009 after Governor Sarah Palin resigned.Palin stepping down this month. CNN, 2009-07-03. He was sworn in at the Governor's Picnic in Fairbanks, Alaska.Palin to Resign as Governor of Alaska - The Caucus Blog - NYTimes.com Accessed July 3, 2009. After finishing Palin's term, Parnell was elected to a full term as Governor in November 2010, becoming the first unelected Alaska Governor to be later elected in his own right.Election 2010: Alaska Results NPR 10-3-2010 In 2014, he lost re-election to Independent Bill Walker. ==Education== Parnell went to Pacific Lutheran University (B.B.A. 1984) and University of Puget Sound School of Law (now Seattle University School of Law) (J.D. 1987). He is admitted to the bar in both Alaska and Washington D.C. ==References== ==Other websites== * Sean Parnell bio and photos * Sandy Parnell |- Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:Governors of Alaska Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Politicians from California Category:People from Fairbanks, Alaska Category:Lieutenant Governors of Alaska
